data.title: Burnham Holdings' Crown Boiler Company subsidiary enters Chapter 11 bankruptcy to address legacy obligations.
data.description: Crown Boiler Company has initiated a voluntary Chapter 11 process in order to address past commitments, in line with Burnham Holdings' plan to optimize its portfolio and facilitate future expansion. The announcement was made in Lancaster, Pennsylvania on February 27, 2026. Burnham Holdings, Inc. (OTC-Pink: BURCA), the parent company, made this decision as part of its long-term growth strategy.

data.title: Chicago Mayor Brandon Johnson discusses student success and human rights at Northeastern Illinois University on Feb 27, 2026.
data.description: On February 27, 2026, Brandon Johnson, the 57th mayor of Chicago, participated in a Lakeside Chat at Northeastern Illinois University (NEIU) to discuss civic leadership, human rights, and challenges encountered by college students. The visit aimed to address issues relevant to the community and encourage dialogue on important topics. The event attracted a significant audience and sparked thoughtful conversations on key issues affecting students and society.

data.title: RevolutionEHR introduces RevPay, an embedded payments solution to enhance revenue collection in optometry practices.
data.description: In San Diego, RevolutionEHR, a top optometry-focused operating platform, unveiled RevPay, their new integrated payments solution. RevPay aims to streamline payment processes for practices, facilitating better revenue recovery. This innovative solution links payments directly to RevolutionEHR's AI-powered platform, merging checkout, patient records, engagement, and reporting into a cohesive workflow. By incorporating payments into the platform's intelligence engine, RevPay enhances efficiency and revenue generation for practices.
